Query Structure

Select

Goal Formula Example
Select all data SELECT *
FROM table name;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons;
Select specific data SELECT column names
FROM table name;		 SELECT LastName, FirstName
FROM Persons;
Select distinct cases SELECT DISTINCT column names
FROM table name;		 SELECT DISTINCT LastName
FROM Persons
Perform a function on the data before returning it:
- AVG()
- MAX()
- MIN()
- SUM()		 SELECT AggFunc(column name)
FROM table name;		 SELECT AVG(Age)
FROM Persons;
Count rows


Count non-nulls


Count distinct values		 SELECT COUNT()
FROM table name;

SELECT COUNT(column name)
FROM table name;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT column name)
FROM table name;		 SELECT COUNT()
FROM Persons;

SELECT COUNT(Email)
FROM Persons;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT LastName)
FROM Persons;
Select element of date SELECT TimeFunc(column name)
FROM table name;		 SELECT MONTH(Birthday)
FROM Persons;

Where

Goal Formula Example
Filter on single value
- =
- <>
- >
- >=
- <
- <=		 SELECT *
FROM table name
WHERE expression;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE FirstName = ‘Ryan’;

SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE FirstName = ‘Ryan’ AND LastName = ‘Brenner’;

SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE FirstName = ‘Bryan’ OR FirstName = ‘Brian’;

SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE (FirstName = ‘Bryan’ OR FirstName = ‘Brian’) AND LastName = ‘Brenner’;
Filter with an inclusive range SELECT *
FROM table name
WHERE column name BETWEEN a AND b		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE Age BETWEEN 18 AND 25;
Filter with a set SELECT *
FROM table name
WHERE column name IN (list)		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE FirstName IN(‘John’, ‘Paul’, ‘Ringo’, ‘George’);
Search for a pattern
- Single wildcard = _
- Unlimited wildcard = %		 SELECT *
FROM table name
WHERE column name LIKE pattern;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE FirstName LIKE ‘Br_an’;

SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE FirstName LIKE ‘Kath%’;

SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE FirstName LIKE ‘%ael’;
!!!Avoid Case Errors!!! SELECT *
FROM table name
WHERE LCASE column name expression;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE LCASE LastName = ‘macdonald’;
Filter nulls SELECT *
FROM table name
WHERE column name IS NULL;

SELECT *
FROM table name
WHERE column name IS NOT NULL;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE SurveyResponse IS NULL;

SELECT *
FROM Persons
WHERE Email IS NOT NULL;

Order

Goal Formula Example
Order the result SELECT *
FROM table name
ORDER BY column name;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
ORDER BY LastName;
Ascending and descending SELECT *
FROM table name
ORDER BY column name ASC;

SELECT *
FROM table name
ORDER BY column name DESC;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons
ORDER BY Year DESC;

SELECT *
FROM Persons
ORDER BY LastName DESC, FirstName ASC;

Group

Goal Formula Example
Aggregate by group SELECT AggFunc(column name 1), column name 2
FROM table name
GROUP BY column name 2;		 SELECT AVG(Age), Team
FROM Persons
GROUP BY Team;
Filter after grouping SELECT AggFunc(column name 1), column name 2
FROM table name
GROUP BY column name 2
HAVING expression;		 SELECT AVG(Age), Team
FROM Persons
GROUP BY Team
HAVING AVG(Age) < 30;

Naming

Goal Formula Example
Create a column alias SELECT column name AS alias
FROM table name;		 SELECT LastName AS Family, FirstName AS Name
FROM Persons;
Create a table alias SELECT *
FROM table name AS alias;		 SELECT *
FROM Persons AS Members;
Create masks SELECT *
CASE
      WHEN condition 1 THEN result 1
      WHEN condition 2 THEN result 2
ELSE result 3
END
AS alias
FROM table name;		 SELECT *
CASE
      WHEN Age < 18 THEN ‘Child’
      WHEN Age > 65 THEN ‘Senior’
      ELSE ‘Adult’
END
AS AgeGroup
FROM Persons;

Joins

Goal Formula Example
SELECT a.column1, b.column2
FROM table1 AS a
_ JOIN table2 as b
ON a.key = b.key;		 SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.PhoneNumber
FROM Persons AS a
LEFT JOIN Phonebook as b
ON a.LastName = b.Family;

SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.PhoneNumber, c.FamilySize
FROM Persons AS a
INNER JOIN Phonebook as b
ON a.LastName = b.Family
RIGHT JOIN Census AS c
ON b.Address = c.Street;

Using multiple keys SELECT a.column1, b.column2
FROM table1 AS a
_ JOIN table2 as b
ON a.key1 = b.key1 AND a.key2 = b.key2;		 SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.PhoneNumber
FROM Persons AS a
LEFT JOIN Phonebook as b
ON a.LastName = b.Surname AND a.FirstName = b.Name;
Using the same key name SELECT a.column1, b.column2
FROM table1 AS a
_ JOIN table2 as b
USING (key);		 SELECT a.FirstName, a.LastName, b.PhoneNumber
FROM Persons AS a
LEFT JOIN Phonebook as b
USING (LastName);

Unions

Goal Formula Example
Stack frames with the same columns
SQL query 1 SetFunc SQL query 2; SELECT DISTINCT LastName
FROM Members2017
UNION
SELECT DISTINCT LastName
FROM Members2018;

SELECT DISTINCT LastName
FROM Members2017
INTERSECT
SELECT DISTINCT LastName
FROM Members2018;

Subqueries

Inside a WHERE clause

SELECT item, stat  
FROM data  
WHERE stat <  
  (SELECT AVG(stat)  
   FROM data);
#Games with more than average goals

query <- "

SELECT date, home_goal, away_goal
FROM matches_2013_2014
WHERE (home_goal + away_goal) >
  (SELECT AVG(home_goal + away_goal)
   FROM matches_2013_2014);
           
"

dbGetQuery(con, query)
date home_goal away_goal
2013-12-14 6 3
2014-03-22 3 6
2013-10-30 7 3 


SELECT *  
FROM dataset1  
WHERE item IN  
  (SELECT item  
   FROM dataset2);
#Teams without a home game 

query <- "

SELECT team_long_name, team_short_name
FROM teams
WHERE team_id NOT IN
  (SELECT DISTINCT hometeam_id
   FROM matches_2013_2014);
           
"

dbGetQuery(con, query)

Inside a FROM Clause

SELECT *
FROM (SELECT key, a.col1, b.col2, derivedcol
      FROM dataset1 AS a
      INNER JOIN dataset2 AS b
      USING (key))
WHERE derivedcol > value
#Countries with high-scoring matches

query <- "

SELECT c.name AS country_name, COUNT(m.id) AS matches
FROM country as c
INNER JOIN (SELECT country_id, id
            FROM matches_2013_2014
            WHERE (home_goal + away_goal) >= 10) AS m
ON c.id = m.country_id
GROUP BY country_name;
"

dbGetQuery(con, query)
country_name matches
Spain 4
England 3
Germany 1


Inside a SELECT Clause

SELECT item,
  (SELECT derviedcol
   FROM dataset2) AS derivedcol 
FROM dataset1;
#Comparing team average to overall average 

query <- "

SELECT c.name AS country_name, 
       ROUND(AVG(m.home_goal + m.away_goal), 2) AS avg_goals,
       ROUND(AVG(m.home_goal + m.away_goal), 2) - (SELECT AVG(home_goal + away_goal
                                                   FROM matches_2013_2014)) AS diff
FROM country as c
INNER JOIN matches_2013_2014 AS m
ON c.id = m.country_id
GROUP BY country_name;
           
"

dbGetQuery(con, query)
country_name avg_goals diff
Switzerland 2.89 0.12
Poland 2.64 -0.13
Netherlands 3.20 0.43

Advanced Querying

Count a Case When

query <- "

SELECT user_id,
  COUNT(CASE WHEN message LIKE '%!%' THEN 'Excited Tweet' END) as 'Excited',
  COUNT(CASE WHEN message LIKE '%?%' THEN 'Question' END) as 'Question'
FROM comments
GROUP BY user_id;
           
"

dbGetQuery(con, query)
user_id Excited Question
1 2 0
2 0 0
3 0 1
4 1 0
5 0 0
6 2 0
7 2 0 
query <- "

SELECT tweat_id,
  ROUND(AVG(CASE WHEN message LIKE '%!%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 2) as 'Excited',
  ROUND(AVG(CASE WHEN message LIKE '%?%' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 2) as 'Question'
FROM comments
GROUP BY tweat_id;
"

dbGetQuery(con, query)
tweat_id Excited Question
49 0.33 0.33
75 1.00 0.00
77 0.50 0.00
87 1.00 0.00
88 0.50 0.00
